Introduced
Second Regular Session 124th General Assembly (2026)
SENATE CONCURRENT
RESOLUTION No. _____
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION honoring the
2 International Brotherhood of Electrical Workers Local 481 on
3 63 years of lighting Monument Circle.
4 Whereas, The Soldiers and Sailors Monument was
5 constructed between 1888 and 1901 and quickly became an
6 iconic symbol of Indianapolis;
7 Whereas, On December 2, 1962, the Soldiers and Sailors
8 Monument was transformed into "the world's largest Christmas
9 tree" when the local International Brotherhood of Electrical
10 Workers (IBEW) illuminated the 246-foot-tall monument in
11 front of a crowd of 10,000 with 6,000 multi-colored lights,
12 weighing 3,220 pounds and with visibility from an estimated
13 twenty miles away;
14 Whereas, Every October since 1962, IBEW 481 volunteer
15 retirees dedicate their time and energy at the Indiana State
16 Fairgrounds by hand checking each of the 4,784 multi-color
17 light bulbs attached to 52 garland strands hung for the Circle
18 of Lights;
19 Whereas, Each November, over 300 IBEW volunteers
20 donate their time to install the Circle of Lights, which typically
21 takes six hours;
22 Whereas, Over the years, the act of lighting the Soldiers
23 and Sailors monument has transformed from a tree gimmick in
24 favor of "The Circle of Lights", a massive effort to create
25 lasting memories through a free event the day after
2026 RC 1514/DI JR

2
1 Thanksgiving each year;
2 Whereas, Each January, over 200 IBEW volunteers donate
3 their time to help take down the Circle of Lights, which
4 typically takes five hours; and
5 Whereas, Regularly drawing crowds of over 100,000
6 people, the Circle of Lights is a beloved annual tradition that
7 signals the start of the holiday season in Indianapolis, built on
8 the selfless hours of work and dedication of IBEW 481
9 volunteers: Therefore,
10 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly
11 of the State of Indiana, the House of Representatives
12 concurring:
13 SECTION 1. That the Indiana General Assembly honors the
14 International Brotherhood of Electrical Workers Local 481 on
15 63 years of lighting Monument Circle and thanks them for
16 decades of bringing holiday cheer to Indianapolis.
17 SECTION 2. The Secretary of the Senate is hereby directed
18 to transmit copies of this Resolution to the International
19 Brotherhood of Electrical Workers Local 481.
2026 RC 1514/DI JR

